   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Future Enhancements
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,706:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 1. Project Overview
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PanicSell
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,707:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  is a personal-use web application that connects to a user
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,708:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: '
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,717:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: s Zerodha brokerage account via the Kite
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,722:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Connect API. It provides a clean dashboard to view all equity holdings with real-time profit/loss data, and enables
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,723:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: rapid liquidation of stocks — either individually selected or the entire portfolio — with a single action.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,726:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The tool is designed for moments of market panic, where speed of execution matters and manually selling each
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: stock through a trading platform is too slow.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,727:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 2. Problem Statement 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: &
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,728:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  Motivation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,735:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: During sharp market downturns, retail investors on platforms like Zerodha must sell each stock individually —
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,736:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: navigating to the stock, entering quantity, confirming the order. With a portfolio of 15–20 stocks, this can take several
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: minutes.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: PanicSell solves this by providing:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,737:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,738:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Batch selling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — select multiple stocks and sell them all at once
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,739:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: One-click full liquidation
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,740:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — a single 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,741:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Panic Sell All
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,742:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  button to exit every position
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: l
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,743:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Instant execution
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,744:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  — market orders placed programmatically via API, no manual form-filling
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 3. Architecture
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,745:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: The application follows a standard client-server architecture:
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,746:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: ┌──────────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐       ┌──────────────────┐
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,754:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  React Frontend  │──────▶│  FastAPI Backend  │──────▶│  Zerodha Kite    │
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: │  localhost:5173  │  API  │  localhost:8000   │  SDK  │  api.kite.trade  │
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,761:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: └──────────────────┘       └──────────────────┘       └──────────────────┘
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Vite proxies all 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: /api/*
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,762:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  requests from the frontend to the backend during development.
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Data Flow
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  1 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,763:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User opens the app in browser → frontend loads from Vite dev server
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  2 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User clicks 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,770:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Connect Zerodha
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: "
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,771:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  → redirected to Kite OAuth login page
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  3 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: After login, Kite redirects back to backend callback with a request token
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,772:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  4 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Backend exchanges request token for access token (valid ~24 hours)
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,773:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  5 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: Frontend fetches holdings via backend → backend calls Kite API → returns processed data
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,774:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment:  6 
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,775:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: User triggers sell → backend places market sell orders via Kite API → returns results
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: 4. Tech Stack
   DEBUG: 2026-03-13 17:58:04,776:      pdf_renderer.py:  470: printSegment: | Layer | Technology | Purpose |
